This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the evaluation of machine translation, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI) and deep learning models (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of pairwise ranking experiments, which is a common evaluation method in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the need to improve the quality of machine translation, which can be achieved through the use of neural networks and other optimization techniques (cs.NE).
